This paper is about structured prediction using neural networks and large-margin training criteria. The paper discusses multi-label classification, sequence labeling, and part-of-speech tagging, which are all topics that fall under the categories of machine learning (cs.LG), natural language processing (cs.CL), computer vision (cs.CV), and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions conditional random fields, which is a topic in the category of cryptography and security (cs.CR).
